---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Window Replacement Berwick 3806 | Aluminium, Timber, Sliding Doors | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Window and sliding-door replacement in Berwick 3806 — for 90s–2000s brick-veneer homes, Edenrise estate new builds and old-Berwick heritage cottages. Single and double-glaze, AS 2047, free measure."
  canonical="https://berwickwindowreplacement.com.au/berwick/">

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Berwick 3806 &middot; old Berwick &middot; Edenrise &middot; Berwick Springs</span>
      <h1>Window replacement in <span class="accent">Berwick</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Berwick splits cleanly into three window jobs: original-Berwick
        heritage cottages along High Street with rotting timber sash; the
        big 1990s&ndash;2000s brick-veneer estates (Berwick Springs, Berwick
        Waters, around Akoonah Park) with chalky single-glaze aluminium; and
        the new-build estates north of the freeway (Edenrise, Eden Park) where
        owners are upgrading the standard-spec builder windows to double-glaze
        or punching out the back wall for bigger sliding doors.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book a free measure</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Berwick</span>
      <h2>The Berwick window story.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>The chalky-aluminium era (built 1992&ndash;2010).</h3>
        <p>
          Roughly 60% of our Berwick jobs are the same house: 4-bed brick-veneer
          on a 600&ndash;750m&sup2; block, builder-spec mid-range aluminium
          frames from the era, single-glazed, white powder coat now gone chalky,
          rubber gaskets hardened, sliding-window rollers either jammed or
          screeching. Condensation streaks on the inside of every window in
          July and August. We re-window the whole house in two&ndash;four days
          for $14K&ndash;$22K including a double-glaze upgrade, and the
          difference in the next winter is instantly obvious &mdash; warmer
          rooms, no condensation, no mould reforming on the architraves.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Edenrise &amp; Eden Park new builds (2018&ndash;2024).</h3>
        <p>
          Newer estate homes around Edenrise typically come with thicker
          aluminium frames and energy-rated glass already &mdash; the windows
          are fine. What owners ask us about here is upgrading the standard
          2.4m living-room sliding door to a 3.6m or 4.2m stacker for a proper
          indoor-outdoor connection, or punching a bifold across the family
          room. Standard new-build sliding door: $2,500&ndash;$3,500. Stacker
          upgrade: $4,500&ndash;$6,500. Bifold: $6,000&ndash;$9,000.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Heritage cottages around High Street &amp; old Berwick.</h3>
        <p>
          The original Berwick township homes &mdash; weatherboard or
          double-brick cottages with timber sash windows &mdash; need a
          like-for-like timber replacement, not aluminium. Council
          planning prefers it, and an aluminium frame on a Victorian
          cottage looks wrong from the street. Stegbar Timber and Trend
          Timber both make new sash windows that match the old
          profiles. Cost is higher ($1,200&ndash;$2,400/window) but the
          house stays original-looking and you get modern weather seals.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Berwick jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Full-house re-window, 12&ndash;15 windows, single-glaze ($12K&ndash;$18K)</li>
          <li>Full-house re-window with double-glaze upgrade ($16K&ndash;$25K)</li>
          <li>Single 2.4m sliding-door replacement ($2.5K&ndash;$4K)</li>
          <li>Stacker-door upgrade 3.6m for indoor-outdoor flow ($4.5K&ndash;$6.5K)</li>
          <li>Bathroom + ensuite + kitchen awnings only (4&ndash;6 windows, $2.5K&ndash;$5K)</li>
          <li>Heritage timber sash replacement (per window $1.2K&ndash;$2.4K)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/cranbourne/">Cranbourne</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/narre-warren/">Narre Warren</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/hampton-park/">Hampton Park</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/endeavour-hills/">Endeavour Hills</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/city-of-casey/">All City of Casey</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Berwick window measure-up.</h2>
        <p>Single-glaze vs double-glaze priced both ways. Brand samples on the day.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
